claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A multi‐row table comparing Flublok Quadrivalent (N=4303) and a comparator vaccine (N=4301) on outcomes including all rtPCR‐positive influenza, influenza A, influenza B, and culture‐confirmed protocol‐defined influenza‐like illness. Columns report event counts (n), attack rates (% n/N), relative risk (RR), and relative vaccine efficacy (rVE % with 95% CI). The table presents clinical efficacy outcomes (attack rates, relative risk, and relative vaccine efficacy) but contains no data or commentary on antigenic matching to WHO‐ or FDA‐selected flu strains, so it does not support the claim. Note: Analysis limited to visible table; no section on antigenic characterization is shown.
